# {{brandName}}

Static campaign SPA generated by `@bonkit/airdrop-studio`.

## Commands

```bash
pnpm install              # Install dependencies
pnpm dev                  # Vite dev server with hot reload
pnpm build                # TypeScript check + production build
pnpm preview              # Preview production build locally
airdrop-studio . # Re-open this workspace in the studio
```

{{runtimeDependencySection}}

## Configuration

For visual editing, re-open the studio with `airdrop-studio .`

For code-level changes, edit these files in order of preference:

1. `src/layout-config.ts` — labels, visibility toggles, layout options
2. `src/theme.ts` — color tokens, fonts, radius
3. `.env` — RPC endpoint, deployment URL
4. `src/App.tsx` — switch layout, adjust providers
5. `src/layouts/` — modify layout components

> **Avoid editing `campaign.config.json` directly.** It is validated by a Zod schema. Invalid edits will break the app and prevent the studio from reopening this workspace. Use the studio or edit `src/layout-config.ts` instead.

### Environment variables

Configure via `.env`:

```
VITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com
VITE_SITE_URL=https://airdrop.example.com
```

- `VITE_RPC_URL` — Solana RPC endpoint
- `VITE_SITE_URL` — Deployment URL. Set before production build for social sharing links (OG tags, canonical) to work correctly.

## Deployment

```bash
pnpm build
# Upload dist/ to your hosting provider
```

### Requirements

- **HTTPS is required.** Solana wallet extensions refuse to connect on plain HTTP. All major static hosts (Vercel, Netlify, CloudFlare Pages, GitHub Pages) serve HTTPS by default.
- **Never deploy the `.bonkit/` directory.** It contains recipient wallet addresses and studio workspace state.

### GitHub Pages (sub-path)

If deploying to `https://username.github.io/repo-name/`, set the Vite base path:

```ts
// vite.config.ts
export default defineConfig({
  base: "/repo-name/",
  // ...existing config
})
```
